<Link id="l00006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="6"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="7"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="8"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The code below implements dead store elimination using MemorySSA. It uses</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the following general approach: given a MemoryDef, walk upwards to find</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// clobbering MemoryDefs that may be killed by the starting def. Then check</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that there are no uses that may read the location of the original MemoryDef</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in between both MemoryDefs. A bit more concretely:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For all MemoryDefs StartDef:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 Get the next dominating clobbering MemoryDef (MaybeDeadAccess) by walking</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    upwards.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 Check that there are no reads between MaybeDeadAccess and the StartDef by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    checking all uses starting at MaybeDeadAccess and walking until we see</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    StartDef.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 3 For each found CurrentDef, check that:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   1 There are no barrier instructions between CurrentDef and StartDef (like</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       throws or stores with ordering constraints).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   2 StartDef is executed whenever CurrentDef is executed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   3 StartDef completely overwrites CurrentDef.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 4 Erase CurrentDef from the function and MemorySSA.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1102"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173a24895aa26eff0c4648c9a58c9b8c8f9c">OW&#95;None</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1103"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173acebc97682d8036254b6ee04910656525">OW&#95;Unknown</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1104"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1105"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1106"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Okay, we have stores to two completely different pointers.  Try to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1107"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// decompose the pointer into a &quot;base + constant&#95;offset&quot; form.  If the base</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1108"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pointers are equal, then we can reason about the two stores.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1109"><span class="doxyHighlight">    DeadOff = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1110"><span class="doxyHighlight">    KillingOff = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1111"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;DeadBasePtr =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1112"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a3ac5d9eb48038aa973017317279eadf5">GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset</a>(DeadPtr, DeadOff, <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/dsestate/#af22719f6b4218045e44871a8c6d82f4d">DL</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1113"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;KillingBasePtr =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1114"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a3ac5d9eb48038aa973017317279eadf5">GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset</a>(KillingPtr, KillingOff, <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/dsestate/#af22719f6b4218045e44871a8c6d82f4d">DL</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1115"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1116"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the base pointers still differ, we have two completely different</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1117"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// stores.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01118" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1118"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (DeadBasePtr != KillingBasePtr)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1119"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173acebc97682d8036254b6ee04910656525">OW&#95;Unknown</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1120"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1121"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The killing access completely overlaps the dead store if and only if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1122"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// both start and end of the dead one is &quot;inside&quot; the killing one:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1123"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|--dead--|&lt;-&gt;|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1124"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |-----killing------|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Accesses may overlap if and only if start of one of them is &quot;inside&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// another one:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|--dead--|&lt;--------&gt;|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |-------killing--------|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//           OR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |-------dead-------|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|---killing---|&lt;-----&gt;|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We have to be careful here as &#42;Off is signed while &#42;.Size is unsigned.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Check if the dead access starts &quot;not before&quot; the killing one.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (DeadOff &gt;= KillingOff) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the dead access ends &quot;not after&quot; the killing access then the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// dead one is completely overwritten by the killing one.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (uint64&#95;t(DeadOff - KillingOff) + DeadSize &lt;= KillingSize)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173a2d4a746f8b3f9492889f9232063d86f8">OW&#95;Complete</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If start of the dead access is &quot;before&quot; end of the killing access</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// then accesses overlap.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ((uint64&#95;t)(DeadOff - KillingOff) &lt; KillingSize)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173aca58bbedad54ea965c6413e5ba085138">OW&#95;MaybePartial</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If start of the killing access is &quot;before&quot; end of the dead access then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// accesses overlap.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1148"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ((uint64&#95;t)(KillingOff - DeadOff) &lt; DeadSize) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
